<br>
...I totally agree with you on this.  First off, let me say, I've always had a great deal of respect for you, for how you roleplay and how intense you are about it.  <br>
...For myself, I've had some excellent roleplay on this server.<br>
I've changed things up lately, got bored being this brooding, grim, &quot;hand of death&quot; type character.  <br>
...To let you know, I enjoy roleplaying with you, it adds a new color and many new possible angles that I can't get by killing paladins and fighting with skrathis (no offense meant at all to them, I've had some great RP with them, I just mean I have been wanting to try something different).  <br>
...There was a point here somewhere, I just forgot what it was.  oh yeah.  I too, like intense roleplay.  I too, sometimes get extreme with it.  As long as I know its in character, there is NOTHING you can say or do that will OOC offend me.  In turn, anything I do is IC, I mean no offense or harm in real life.<br>
...Having said that......<br>
...there is a low down, back stabbing, lying, cheating, traitorous lizard out there.  His name is Notuanot.  He hunts with rangers.  He sleeps with high elves.  If the price is right, he protects the servants of the prime healer, he does errands for the Veeshan, he fights for the dwarves of Thurgadin.  The principals of evil, of good, or justice or virtue, of destruction and hate and fear, these mean nothing to him.  All he cares about is what he wants.  He will take it from the half dead Tier Dal shadowknight fighting for her food in Nektulos forest.  He will take it from the mouths of starving gnomish children.  He will take it from your mother.  He will take it from you.  And right now, he wants your green eyes, and will try to rip them out of your skull!<br>
...What will you do?  <br>
<br>
 <p>This is my chosen path<BR>
There is no other<BR>
I am...<BR>
What I am<BR>

<font face="arial"><a
