<br>
So many people searching for reasons to feel some emotion, and convincing themselves that getting angry over perceived &quot;offences&quot; can substitute for that...<br>
<br>
Everyone wants to get angry about injustices aimed at them. All it takes is the slightest slip and **BAM** You're in a lawsuit.<br>
<br>
In order to co-exist with others (ie, function within a society), there needs to be a basic tolerance level that every agrees with and adheres to, while recognizing that the entire world does not, in fact, revolve around each one of us.<br>
<br>
I think this got lost somewhere along the way, which is why we've got so much whining going on nowadays.<br>
<br>
You're just lucky you didnt end up with a lawsuit on your hands Shin.<br>
<br>
Domenic Dominion<br>
